cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a distributed graph layout strategy for improving the performance of distributed memory graph computations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the layout of vertex and edge arrays and the ordering of identifiers. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of a distributed SPARQL query processing engine. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses communication time and inter-task load balance. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper analyzes the impact of graph layout on the performance of graph analytics workloads.
